      <section eId="sec_19_13_3">
        <num>19-13-3</num>
        <content>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1981, p. 880, § 3; Ga. L. 1982, p. 3, § 19; Ga. L. 1984, p. 542, § 1; Ga. L. 1985, p. 983, § 1; Ga. L. 1988, p. 320, § 3; Ga. L. 1988, p. 1248, § 1; Ga. L. 1994, p. 1270, § 7; Ga. L. 1996, p. 883, § 5; Ga. L. 2018, p. 969, § 1/HB 834.)</p>
          <p>The 2018 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2018, added "and such order shall remain in effect until the court issues an order dismissing such order or a hearing as set forth in subsection (c) of this Code section occurs, whichever occurs first" at the end of the last sentence of subsection (b); in subsection (c), substituted "but not later" for "but in no case later" in the first sentence, and inserted "of the filing of the petition" in the middle of the last sentence; and added subsection (d).</p>
        </content>
      </section>
